    "InternLM2 and its fine-tuned version, InternLM2 FT, delivered the highest scores among the individual models at 68.8, indicating a stronger semantic alignment.",
    "On the other hand, the underperformance of all open-source LLMs in extracting \"Evaluation metrics\" and \"Limitations\" can be principally attributed to two specific challenges.",
    "First, the task of extracting \"Evaluation metrics\" often involves identifying multiple distinct indicators such as accuracy, precision, and recall, which may be intricately described within the text.",
    "Open-source LLMs may struggle with this multifaceted extraction, leading to the omission of certain indicators that are critical for a comprehensive evaluation.",
    "Second, the extraction of \"Limitations\" presents its unique set of difficulties, as not all authors explicitly mention limitations within their articles."
